<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-424] A class providing JUnit&apos;s suite() method need not itself implement Test. But Surefire ignores the suite if it doesn&apos;t.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-424</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Often, there is one test method per test case. JUnit allows a test class to be more flexible: It may generate a test suite at test run time, which may contain any number of tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JUnit has traditionally required&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a &lt;tt&gt;public static suite()&lt;/tt&gt; method&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;returning &lt;tt&gt;junit.framework.Test&lt;/tt&gt; (or some type, such as &lt;tt&gt;TestSuite&lt;/tt&gt;, that can be cast to &lt;tt&gt;Test&lt;/tt&gt; ).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In addition to these JUnit requirements, Surefire imposes one more requirement:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the class that contains the &lt;tt&gt;suite()&lt;/tt&gt; method needs to itself implement &lt;tt&gt;junit.framework.Test&lt;/tt&gt; .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If that additional requirement is not met, the &lt;tt&gt;suite()&lt;/tt&gt; method is not called, but silently ignored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Surefire should not impose this additional requirement, but call any &lt;tt&gt;suite()&lt;/tt&gt; method that returns something that can be cast to &lt;tt&gt;junit.framework.Test&lt;/tt&gt; , in any test class.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
